Crowds of the faithful gathered outside the Pretoria magistrate's court as the bail application for their prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife is postponed again. Tshegohaco Moagi reports. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - The case against self-proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary has been postponed to Friday. Magistrate Thandi Thelede said she's unavailable on the other days of this week. READ: Bushiri and wife back in court to hear bail outcome Magistrate Thelede noted with concern that there were a large number of people outside on Monday who were not social distancing. She stated she cannot risk having large crowds outside without sufficient time to attend to the matter. READ: Bushiri's SA permanent residency in question The couple and a third-accused, Landiwe Ntlokoane, are facing charges of fraud, theft and money laundering of over R100-million. Last week, Mary Bushiri was arrested by the Hawks while her husband and Ntlokoane handed themselves over. The accused will remain in custody until Friday.